Accessible tickets are available online directly via Ticketmaster. 

To see the availability of Accessible Tickets that can be purchased online check the appropriate 'Type' from the list.
'Wheelchair Accessible' are for wheelchair users only. 
'Ambulant Disabled' positions are located within general seated areas and tiered seating and have been allocated due to their ease of access.

The accessible ticket policy limits one free carer ticket to each accessible ticket purchased. Patrons who have any questions
about booking tickets, or require further assistance please email access@ticketmaster.co.uk (subject to availability and we expect tickets to sell out quickly online).

By purchasing an accessible ticket, you confirm you or a member of your party require this position. Proof of eligibility/disability must be provided before the event - you will be contacted by Ticketmaster no later than 72 hours after your order.

Tickets may be cancelled if misuse is suspected/found.

All Accessible Tickets for this event are sold by Wembley Stadium and can be booked by calling 0800 093 0824.

For Wheelchair/Ease of Access seating, please call the venue on 0800 093 0824. Before purchasing your tickets, the Venue will require proof of disability to ensure that all allocated seating is being provided to the guests who require it.

If you have previously purchased tickets with them and already have a customer number, you do not need to send in proof of disability again. If you cannot remember your customer number, they can look it up when you call.

venues.name: Wembley Stadium

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets left for collection can be picked up from the box office at the venue on the day of the event. Please note that customers collecting tickets must bring Photo ID with them as well as their credit/debit cards and Ticketmaster reference number.

venues.parkingDetail: Please use the official Stadium car parks if driving to the venue, available to pre-book by visiting www.wembleyofficialparking.com. A resident’s only parking permit scheme operates in the Wembley area on Stadium event days. Illegally parked vehicles will be fined by Brent Council and may be towed away. For details of the restrictions visit www.brent.gov.uk/wembley
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Wembley Stadium has wheelchair accessible spaces with an equal number of adjacent seats available for Personal Assistants. Wembley Stadium also have enhanced amenity seats for ambulant disabled visitors, each disabled seating area has a dedicated member of staff. Staff on disabled bays are specifically trained to meet the requirements of disabled visitors. Wembley Stadium has 147 accessible toilets within the Stadium, all accessible via RADAR keys. There are also 193 Ambulant Toilets. The toilets are available on all levels. Please see the event sale page for information on booking accessible tickets for your chosen event

generalInfo.generalRule: No cameras, video cameras or audio recording devices.
generalInfo.childRule: Seated area: No children under 2 years old. Standing area: No children under 14 years old. All children under 16 years old must be accompanied by an adult.

For Wheelchair/Ease of Access seating, please call the venue on 0800 093 0824. Before purchasing your tickets, the Venue will require proof of disability to ensure that all allocated seating is being provided to the guests who require it.

If you have previously purchased tickets with them and already have a customer number, you do not need to send in proof of disability again. If you cannot remember your customer number, they can look it up when you call.

ticketLimit.info: There is a maximum of 4 (four) tickets per access code.

venues.name: Wembley Stadium

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets left for collection can be picked up from the box office at the venue on the day of the event. Please note that customers collecting tickets must bring Photo ID with them as well as their credit/debit cards and Ticketmaster reference number.

venues.parkingDetail: Please use the official Stadium car parks if driving to the venue, available to pre-book by visiting www.wembleyofficialparking.com. A resident’s only parking permit scheme operates in the Wembley area on Stadium event days. Illegally parked vehicles will be fined by Brent Council and may be towed away. For details of the restrictions visit www.brent.gov.uk/wembley
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Wembley Stadium has wheelchair accessible spaces with an equal number of adjacent seats available for Personal Assistants. Wembley Stadium also have enhanced amenity seats for ambulant disabled visitors, each disabled seating area has a dedicated member of staff. Staff on disabled bays are specifically trained to meet the requirements of disabled visitors. Wembley Stadium has 147 accessible toilets within the Stadium, all accessible via RADAR keys. There are also 193 Ambulant Toilets. The toilets are available on all levels. Please see the event sale page for information on booking accessible tickets for your chosen event

generalInfo.generalRule: No cameras, video cameras or audio recording devices.

accessibility.info:
Wheelchair Accessible seats are located on Levels 1, 3 and 5. 
Ambulant Disabled, Sight Impaired, and Hearing Impaired seats are located on East Level 1. There is a lift up to concourse level, and then approximately 7 steps down to rows.
Wheelchair Accessible and Sight Impaired tickets may be purchased with a complimentary attendant ticket. If you have not registered your requirement for a carer with Ticketmaster, this attendant ticket may be charged at a later date. All such tickets are sold only in pairs in a 1/1 ratio.
Ambulant Disabled and Hearing Impaired tickets can be purchased up to the event limit (4). If you need these seats and have registered a requirement for a carer with Ticketmasters accessible database, you can request a purchased ticket be transferred to a complimentary attendant after purchase via your My Account function. (Limits apply.)
If you are purchasing tickets in a 1/1 restricted area, you can also buy up to the event limit in another part of the stadium.

venues.parkingDetail: There are several independently owned parking facilities located within walking distance of Rogers Centre. Prices and availability are managed by the individual proprietors and are not connected with the Blue Jays organization. A limited number of parking spaces are available in the Rogers Centre underground lot for guests with accessibility needs. Reservations are required on game/event days and can be made by calling 416-341-1540. Please have your disability permit number handy for bookings. Cashless payment is required.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seats are subject to the same onsale schedules and ticket availability as standard seating and are sold on a first-come, first-served basis. Fans requiring an accessible seat may also purchase up to three additional seats for their companions (subject to availability) unless otherwise restricted by event-level ticket limits. Fans with accessible needs may enter Rogers Centre through any open gate. Fans requiring accessible support are encouraged to enter through Gate 7, the designated accessible located on the south side of the building (along Bremner Boulevard). Rogers Centre is proud to be a Sensory Inclusive Certified venue by KultureCity. Sensory Bags are available at any Fan Services location. A Sensory Room can also be found at Section 212 behind Fan Services. Additional Info: bluejays.com/accessibility

generalInfo.generalRule: Know Before You Go Gameday Experience: bluejays.com/knowbeforeyougo Know Before You Go Concert Experience: bluejays.com/concerts MOBILE TICKETING Blue Jays and Rogers Centre concert tickets are delivered digitally and must be scanned in at the gate using a mobile device. Display your ticket at the gate through MLB Ballpark app, your Blue Jays Account Manager, or, if you purchased via ticketmaster.ca, the Ticketmaster app. Paper or PDF tickets are not accepted and the Box Office at Rogers Centre is not open for ticket purchases. Mobile support staff will be available to assist fans as required at the gates. GATE ENTRY Gates for Blue Jays games are open 90 minutes before the scheduled game time on weekdays and two hours on weekends. Check bluejays.com/concerts for concert gate information. Fans may enter at any open main gate, however the closest entrance to each fan's seat will be recommended by the ticket app. BAG POLICY Bags are discouraged and will be subject to a security search prior to entry. Only bags smaller than 16 x 16: x 8 are permitted into the ballpark. Bag restrictions and prohibited items for concerts may be different than Blue Jays games; visit bluejays.com/concerts SECURITY MEASURES In order to provide our fans with a safe environment, searches at all entry gates will include the inspection of all items that are carried into the stadium. Everyone entering will be subject to full searches of their person, with the use of walk through metal detectors (WTMD). Other methods include hand-held metal detectors or pat downs. For a list of prohibited items, please visit bluejays.com/ballpark. FAN FEEDBACK The Toronto Blue Jays and Rogers Centre welcome the ideas, comments and suggestions from our fans. It helps us improve the service we provide to our valued fans and fans. Please contact our Fan Services Team by email at fanfeedback@bluejays.com or by phone at (416)341-1000 to submit your feedback/inquiry.
generalInfo.childRule: All fans two (2) years of age or older must have a valid ticket to enter Rogers Centre.
